{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/39219", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/39219/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/39219/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/39219/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/39219", "id": 202309092, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWUyMDIzMDkwOTI=", "number": 39219, "title": "`unresolved name` error when trying to construct a tuple struct through type alias", "user": {"login": "d3lio", "id": 6381604, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjYzODE2MDQ=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/6381604?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/d3lio", "html_url": "https://github.com/d3lio", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/d3lio/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/d3lio/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/d3lio/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/d3lio/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/d3lio/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/d3lio/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/d3lio/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/d3lio/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/d3lio/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 2, "created_at": "2017-01-21T11:04:03Z", "updated_at": "2017-05-20T02:01:49Z", "closed_at": "2017-05-20T02:01:49Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "When I tried to construct a tuple struct with a type alias it gives me an error like\r\n\r\n```rustc 1.15.0-beta.4 (ad78c04a9 2017-01-18)\r\nerror[E0425]: unresolved name `A`\r\n   |\r\n   |     let a: A = A(5);\r\n   |                ^ unresolved name\r\n```\r\n\r\nExample:\r\n\r\n```Rust\r\nstruct TupleStruct(u8);\r\nstruct NormalStruct {\r\n    field: u8\r\n}\r\ntype A = TupleStruct;\r\ntype B = NormalStruct;\r\n\r\nfn main() {\r\n    let a: A = A(5); // Error\r\n    let b: B = B { field: 5 }; // This is fine\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf I instead do `let a: A = TupleStruct(5)` the code is compiled perfectly fine.\r\nType `B` on the other hand has no problems compiling as it is in this example.\r\n\r\nAnother example would be returning the value from a function\r\n```Rust\r\nstruct TupleStruct(u8);\r\ntype A = TupleStruct;\r\n\r\nimpl A {\r\n    fn new() -> A {\r\n        A(5) // Error\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\nWhat I expect are no compile errors when the tuple struct is constructed through the type alias `A`.\r\n\r\nI've tried this on both 1.14.0 stable and 1.15.0-beta4 in https://play.rust-lang.org and 1.14.0 locally: \r\n\r\n`rustc --version --verbose`:\r\n\r\nrustc 1.14.0 (e8a012324 2016-12-16)\r\nbinary: rustc\r\ncommit-hash: e8a0123241f0d397d39cd18fcc4e5e7edde22730\r\ncommit-date: 2016-12-16\r\nhost: x86_64-pc-windows-msvc\r\nrelease: 1.14.0\r\nLLVM version: 3.9\r\n", "closed_by": {"login": "Mark-Simulacrum", "id": 5047365, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjUwNDczNjU=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5047365?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum", "html_url": "https://github.com/Mark-Simulacrum", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/orgs", "repos_url"